I focused on essential **Linux commands** that help manage files, directories, and user access — a critical foundation for working in cloud environments.


## 🧠 Topics Covered

- 🔐 **`chmod`** – Used to change file and directory permissions  
- 🛡️ **`chown`** – Used to change the ownership of files and directories  
- 👤 **`adduser`** – Command to add a new user to the system  

---

## 🧪 Sample Commands

# Give read, write, execute permissions to owner, and read/execute to group and others
chmod 755 user
![2025-04-07_18-45](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/fb03259a-e39a-4909-8ffa-5fe04f971e91)

# Change ownership of a file to a specific user and group
chown root:ec2-user user
![2025-04-07_18-50](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/15860d56-3c0e-4906-8937-984029d29761)

# Add a new user
adduser vishal
![2025-04-07_19-13](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8742744c-97a8-4fcc-b714-562358e5811b)
